The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining spectral sparsifiers of graphs in dynamic streams, which involves topics such as data structures, streaming algorithms, linear algebra, and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves sketching techniques, which are commonly used in the subfield of compressed sensing (cs.IT - Information Theory). The use of effective resistance and spectral sparsification also suggests the subfield of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper involves randomized algorithms and probabilistic analysis, which are common in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning). Finally, the use of linear sketches and sparse recovery techniques suggests the subfield of signal processing (cs.SI - Signal Processing).
